{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6618aabf-9952-465b-99d9-6547e15c1868","content":"Here's the migration checklist:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly (MTP produces a standalone executable).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're on xUnit **2.9.3**, the `xunit.runner.mtp` bridge package lets you adopt MTP without upgrading to v3.\n- If you're ready for the full migration, xUnit **v3** (`xunit.v3`) has native MTP support and is the recommended long-term path.\n\nWould you like help updating a specific `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"160faaea-9976-46e9-92ff-af3631130bff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"481F:E621D:3098863:352777B:69FBE1D0"},"id":"2671a472-b32b-440d-abdc-5d73cf75c6bc","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:50:35.036Z","parentId":"00433aa9-6545-425a-8a73-db346d5c88f6"}
